  "metadata": {
    "role": "article",
    "roleHeading": "Article",
    "title": "Downloading and installing additional Xcode components"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Xcode lets you manage optional components yourself so that you can install only the components you use and remove the ones you don’t. For example, install the Simulator runtimes for the devices and operating systems your app runs on, or add support for platforms that you target. You download and install Xcode components in Xcode settings or using the command line.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Developing for visionOS requires a Mac with Apple silicon.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Note",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Manage-Xcode-components-in-settings",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Manage Xcode components in settings",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To manage your components, choose Xcode > Settings and click Components in the toolbar. Xcode shows the installed and enabled components along with the amount of storage you can recover if you remove them.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "downloading-and-installing-components",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "There are three types of components:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "definition": {
                "content": [
                  {
                    "inlineContent": [
                      {
                        "text": "The platforms that you can develop your apps for.",
                        "type": "text"
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ]
              },
              "term": {
                "inlineContent": [
                  {
                    "text": "Platform Support",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "definition": {
                "content": [
                  {
                    "inlineContent": [
                      {
                        "text": "Optional Xcode features you can enable and disable.",
                        "type": "text"
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ]
              },
              "term": {
                "inlineContent": [
                  {
                    "text": "Other Components",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "definition": {
                "content": [
                  {
                    "inlineContent": [
                      {
                        "text": "Simulator runtimes for different devices and OS releases that you can run your app on.",
                        "type": "text"
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ]
              },
              "term": {
                "inlineContent": [
                  {
                    "text": "Other Installed Platforms",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "type": "termList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To download and install a component in any of these sections, click the Get button next to the component.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To remove or disable components you no longer use and recover their storage space, select the component and click the Delete button (-) in the lower-left corner. Then click Delete or Disable in the dialog that appears.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can also install platform support when you create a project by selecting a template and clicking the Get button that appears for platforms that aren’t installed. For more information, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.Xcode/documentation/Xcode/creating-an-xcode-project-for-an-app",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "You can create a new Xcode project or work with an existing Xcode project on a platform that Xcode is installing, but you can’t run or build the project until Xcode finishes downloading and installing the files.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Note",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Install-previously-released-Simulator-runtimes-in-settings",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Install previously released Simulator runtimes in settings",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can get previously released Simulator runtimes in the Components settings. Click the Add button (+) in the lower-left corner, then select a platform to view a list of its available versions. In the dialog that appears, select one or more versions, and click Download & Install.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Install-Simulator-runtimes-from-the-Xcode-run-destination",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Install Simulator runtimes from the Xcode run destination",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "When you open an Xcode project for a platform that doesn’t have any installed Simulator runtimes, Xcode displays a Get button next to the run destination. Click the Get button to download and install the most recent Simulator runtime for that platform.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The run destination in your Xcode project indicates when Xcode is downloading a Simulator runtime. You can select a run destination when Xcode completes the download and installation.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Download-Xcode-components-from-the-command-line",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Download Xcode components from the command line",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can also download components in Terminal using the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "xcodebuild",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " command. For example, use the command line to download Xcode components once and then install them across multiple Mac computers.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To download Simulator runtimes for a specific platform, use this syntax:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "xcodebuild -downloadPlatform <platform> [-exportPath <path>] [-buildVersion <specific-version>]"
          ],
          "syntax": null,
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For example:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "xcodebuild -downloadPlatform iOS -exportPath ~/Downloads"
          ],
          "syntax": null,
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To specify an Xcode version, add the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "-buildVersion",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " option:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "xcodebuild -downloadPlatform iOS -exportPath ~/Downloads -buildVersion 16.0 "
          ],
          "syntax": null,
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To download all the supported platforms for the version of Xcode you select, use this syntax with the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "-downloadAllPlatforms",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " option:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "xcodebuild -downloadAllPlatforms [-exportPath <path>]"
          ],
          "syntax": null,
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Install-downloaded-packages-from-the-command-line",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Install downloaded packages from the command line",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "After you download component packages, you can install them in Terminal with the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "xcodebuild",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " command.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "First, select the version of Xcode you want to use with the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "xcode-select -s <path-to-Xcode>",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " command. Next, run ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "xcodebuild -runFirstLaunch",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " to install any required system components, including the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "simctl",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " utility. Then, run ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "xcodebuild",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " with the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "-importPlatform <simruntime.dmg>",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " option to install the component.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "xcode-select -s /Applications/Xcode-beta.app",
            "xcodebuild -runFirstLaunch",
            "xcodebuild -importPlatform \"~/Downloads/watchOS 9 beta Simulator Runtime.dmg\""
          ],
          "syntax": null,
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Download-and-install-new-hardware-support-in-between-Xcode-releases",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Download and install new hardware support in between Xcode releases",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To download and install hardware support updates in between Xcode releases, use ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "xcodebuild",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " with the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "-runFirstLaunch",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "-checkForNewerComponents",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " options. Before running this command, select the version of Xcode you want to use with the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "xcode-select -s <path-to-Xcode>",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " command.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "xcode-select -s /Applications/Xcode.app",
            "xcodebuild -runFirstLaunch -checkForNewerComponents"
          ],
          "syntax": null,
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "If new components exist, the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "-checkForNewerComponents",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " option stores the files in the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "~/Library/Developer/Packages/",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " directory and installs the components for the Xcode version you select.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
